From: chainonyourdoor <chainonyourdoor@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 19:40:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] sched/fair: add BORE CPU scheduler v5.3.0 (KABI-safe) for android14-6.1

Integration of BORE (Burst-Oriented Response Enhancer) -- partial backport
to v5.3.0 -- by Masahito S <firelzrd@gmail.com> for android14-6.1 (Linux 6.1.x).

Original source: https://github.com/firelzrd/bore-scheduler

Supersedes the previous v5.1.0 import (see git history). This revision:
- Backports v5.1.0 -> v5.1.11 -> v5.3.0 upstream changes (sysctl table
  moved out of kernel/sched/fair.c into kernel/sysctl.c with a
  dedicated sched_bore_update_handler() that re-applies task weights on
  toggle; new sched_burst_exclude_kthreads tunable; sched_fork_bore() now
  takes an explicit \`parent\` argument instead of relying on
  p->real_parent, and is called directly from kernel/fork.c's
  copy_process() rather than through __sched_fork()).
- Fixes a KABI/ABI break present in the v5.1.0 revision: that version
  added new fields to struct sched_entity in the middle of the struct
  (after prev_sum_exec_runtime), shifting the offset of every field
  after it. This silently breaks any prebuilt, KMI-signed vendor module
  that touches sched_entity past that point -- not specific to one SoC
  vendor, it's an ABI violation for any GKI vendor module. Fixed by
  moving all BORE fields into the struct's existing
  ANDROID_KABI_RESERVE(1-4) reserved slots at the end of sched_entity,
  using the official ANDROID_KABI_USE()/_ANDROID_KABI_REPLACE() macros
  instead of a hand-rolled union -- this keeps sizeof(struct sched_entity)
  and every existing field offset identical to a non-BORE GKI build.

Adapted with reference to the public partial-backport-to-5.3.0 work in
chainonyourdoor/android_kernel_common-6.1-ramabondanp (android14-6.1-staging
branch) which independently carried the same v5.1.0 base forward using
this KABI-safe approach.

Changes:
- include/linux/sched.h      : BORE fields via ANDROID_KABI_USE/_REPLACE
  on the existing reserve slots (no ABI break)
- include/linux/sched/task.h : sched_fork_bore() prototype (parent arg)
- init/Kconfig               : SCHED_BORE Kconfig option
- kernel/fork.c              : call sched_fork_bore(p, current) from
  copy_process()
- kernel/sched/core.c        : burst init/inherit/fork logic
- kernel/sched/debug.c       : expose burst score in sched debug output
- kernel/sched/fair.c        : burst score calculation, vruntime penalty
  integration, BORE-tuned scheduling latency/granularity defaults
- kernel/sysctl.c            : BORE sysctl knobs (moved out of fair.c),
  sched_bore_update_handler() reapplies task weights live on toggle

NOTE: hunks below are context-based, not machine-verified against this
repo's exact android14-6.1-staging checkout -- this sandbox has no network
access to android.googlesource.com to test-apply directly. bore.sh already
runs a forward/reverse --dry-run before applying and aborts the build
loudly on any mismatch rather than silently skipping BORE, so a bad hunk
fails the build instead of shipping a half-patched kernel.

Signed-off-by: chainonyourdoor <chainonyourdoor@gmail.com>
---
diff --git a/include/linux/sched.h b/include/linux/sched.h
index 464d41843..8a2c9f1d2 100644
--- a/include/linux/sched.h
+++ b/include/linux/sched.h
@@ -584,10 +584,24 @@ struct sched_entity {
 	struct sched_avg		avg;
 #endif
 
+#ifdef CONFIG_SCHED_BORE
+	ANDROID_KABI_USE(1, u64 burst_time);
+	_ANDROID_KABI_REPLACE(_ANDROID_KABI_RESERVE(2),
+		struct {
+			u8 prev_burst_penalty;
+			u8 curr_burst_penalty;
+			u8 burst_penalty;
+			u8 burst_score;
+		}
+	);
+	ANDROID_KABI_USE2(3, u8 child_burst, u32 child_burst_cnt);
+	ANDROID_KABI_USE(4, u64 child_burst_last_cached);
+#else
 	ANDROID_KABI_RESERVE(1);
 	ANDROID_KABI_RESERVE(2);
 	ANDROID_KABI_RESERVE(3);
 	ANDROID_KABI_RESERVE(4);
+#endif
 };
 
 struct sched_rt_entity {
